used%20me%20substantial%20trauma.%20I%20practically%20lived%20at%20the%20hospital%20and%20was%20thrust%20into%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbecame-my-moms-caregiver-at-age-thirteen-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20role%20of%20caretaker%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226422e652-df15-48d0-ae37-b9ad32d68be0%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20had%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20do%20everything%20again%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEventually%2C%20she%20was%20discharged%20and%20had%20to%20go%20to%20a%20rehab%20facility%20to%20re-learn%20how%20to%20swallow%2C%20eat%2C%20stand%2C%20and%20walk.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20was%20left%20with%20permanent%20cognitive%20impairment%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Falzheimers-vs-dementia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edementia%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20and%20I%20was%20left%20in%20charge%20of%20every%20detail%20of%20her%20life%20%E2%80%94%20her%20finances%2C%20personal%20life%2C%20and%20healthcare%20decisions%20%E2%80%94%20mental%20and%20physical.%20After%20rehab%2C%20I%20had%20to%20move%20her%20into%20an%20assisted%20living%20facility.%20I%20am%20physically%20unable%20to%20care%20for%20her%2C%20nor%20can%20I%20provide%20the%20constant%20supervision%20she%20requires.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFortunately%2C%20she%20is%20the%20type%20of%20person%20who%20is%20easygoing%20and%20positive%2C%20and%20though%20she%20doesn't%20always%20make%20sense%20the%20staff%20enjoy%20her%20and%20take%20good%20care%20of%20her.%20She%20lost%20the%20ability%20to%20understand%20how%20to%20work%20a%20phone%20or%20computer%2C%20and%20cannot%20concentrate%20on%20anything%20so%20she%20lost%20her%20love%20of%20reading%20books.%20But%20she%20has%20TV%2C%20attends%20activities%20when%20she%20can%2C%20and%20I%20take