y%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EChinese%20leader%20Xi%20Jinping%20is%20courting%20trade%20and%20influence%20in%20Europe.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20European%20firms%20in%20China%20report%20dwindling%20confidence%20in%20their%20operations.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20key%20challenge%20EU%20businesses%20face%20is%20in%20attracting%20international%20talent%20to%20China.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EChinese%20leader%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-visit-france-macron-europe-trade-relations-us-tensions-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EXi%20Jinping%20is%20in%20Europe%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20trying%20to%20charm%20his%20way%20to%20more%20trade%2C%20investments%2C%20and%20influence%20in%20France%2C%20Serbia%2C%20and%20Hungary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20pomp%20and%20hype%20over%20Xi's%20trip%2C%20European%20firms%20in%20China%20say%20they%20aren't%20quite%20convinced%20about%20their%20prospects%20in%20the%20country%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.europeanchamber.com.cn%2Fen%2Fpublications-archive%2F1177%2FBusiness_Confidence_Survey_2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEuropean%20Union%20Chamber%20of%20Commerce%20in%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%20report%20released%20on%20Friday.%20Its%20survey%20of%20529%20respondents%20was%20conducted%20in%20January%20and%20February.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20business%20chamber's%20survey%2C%20just%2013%25%20view%20China%20as%20a%20top%20investment%20destination%20%E2%80%94%20a%20record%20low.%20It's%20also%20much%20lower%20than%20the%2027%25%20of%20EU%20firms%20who%20viewed%20China%20as%20a%20top%20investment%20destination%20in%202021%2C%20when%20the%20country%20was%20still%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20on-off%20pandemic%20lockdowns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20economy%20is%20in%20a%20painful%20transition%20from%20its%20reliance%20on%20lower-cost%20manufacturing%20and%20real%20estate%20to%20what%20Xi's%20administration%20calls%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-economy-new-growth-areas-electric-vehicles-batteries-solar-property-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bnew%20three%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20sectors%20of%20electric%20vehicles%2C%20lithium%20batteries%2C%20and%20solar%20cells.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20economic%20drag%20on%20business%20sentiment%20was%20evident%20from%20the%20survey%20results%2C%20with%20more%20than%20two-thirds%20of%20respondents%20saying%20that%20doing%20business%20in%20China%20became%20more%20difficult%20in%202023%20%E2%80%94%20the%20highest%20proportion%20on%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d63dc581-fef4-415b-9ad4-aa436e1e3028%5C%22%3EEU%20firms'%20China%20operations%20are%20'decoupling'%20from%20their%20headquarters%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20the%20gloomy%20economy%20and%20slowing%20demand%20that%20are%20weighing%20on%20investor%20confidence.%20EU%20firms%20have%20also%20started%20to%20%26quot%3Bdecouple%26quot%3B%20their%20operations%20in%20China%20as%20the%20number%20of%20foreign%20nationals%20employed%20locally%20falls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20worrying%20signs%20that%20some%20European%20companies%20are%20either%20silo-ing%20operations%20or%20scaling%20down%20their%20ambitions%20in%20China%20as%20the%20challenges%20they%20face%20start%20to%20outweigh%20the%20benefits%20of%20being%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Jens%20Eskelund%2C%20the%20chamber's%20president%2C%20said%20at%20a%20press%20conference%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Feuropean-firms-souring-china-lobby-group-warns-2024-05-10%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20a%20third%20of%20respondents%20face%20challenges%20attracting%20or%20retaining%20international%20talent%20in%20China%2C%20with%2070%25%20citing%20a%20lack%20of%20willingness%20among%20potential%20candidates%20to%20relocate%20as%20the%20key%20issue%2C%20according%20to%20the%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMembers%20report%20that%20a%20drop%20in%20the%20number%20of%20Europeans%20employed%20by%20their%20China%20operations%20has%20been%20a%20key%20factor%20behind%20the%20trend%20of%20decoupling%20between%20HQs%20and%20China%20operations%2C%20as%20it%20has%20led%20to%20a%20decrease%20in%20mutual%20understanding%20and%20trust%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20makes%20it%20increasingly%20difficult%20for%20the%20China%20operations%20of%20the%20EU%20firms%20to%20get%20approval%20from%20their%20headquarters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20decoupling%20%E2%80%94%20which%20was%20reported%20by%20two-fifths%20of%20respondents%20%E2%80%94%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emeans%20local%20Chinese%20operations%20and%20their%20headquarters%20now%20have%20less%20understanding%20of%20on-the-ground%20realities%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Ba%20dynamic%20that%20is%20being%20exacerbated%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20more%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Ffinance%2Fchinas-top-financial-data-provider-restricts-offshore-access-due-new-rules-2023-05-04%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20restrictions%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20being%20placed%20on%20access%20to%20reliable%20information%20about%20China's%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20European%20business%20chamber%20called%20for%20%26quot%3Bfull%20access%20to%20legitimate%20and%20trustworthy%20sources%20of%20economic%20data%26quot%3B%20in%20its%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWithout%20this%2C%20many%20CEOs%20will%20continue%20to%20feel%20they%20simply%20do%20not%20have%20the%20transparency%20and%20legal%20certainty%20they%20need%20to%20justify%20to%20their%20boards%20that%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20increase%20%E2%80%94%20or%20in%20some%20cases%20even%20maintain%20%E2%80%94%20their%20investments%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20record%20low%2042%25%20of%20EU%20companies%20said%20they%20plan%20t