gle%20is%20currently%20battling%20two%20key%20antitrust%20cases%20over%20its%20search%20engine%20and%20advertising%20tactics.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGoogle%20also%20recently%20settled%20two%20class-action%20lawsuits%20concerning%20privacy%20and%20antitrust%20violations.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20is%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20and%20most%20influential%20companies%2C%20and%20the%20most%20popular%20search%20engine%20by%20far.%20So%20it's%20no%20surprise%20that%20the%20search%20giant's%20rapidly%20evolving%20and%20boundary-pushing%20technology%20would%20attract%20litigation%20over%20the%20course%20of%20its%2025-year%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20has%20been%20sued%20in%20dozens%2C%20if%20not%20hundreds%20of%20high-profile%20controversies%20over%20privacy%2C%20intellectual%20property%2C%20discrimination%2C%20advertising%2C%20and%20even%20defamation%2C%20and%20has%20racked%20up%20both%20wins%20and%20losses%20over%20the%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20Google's%20most%20consequential%20legal%20cases%20have%20occurred%20in%202023%20and%202024%2C%20including%20two%20major%20antitrust%20cases%20and%20several%20class-action%20lawsuits.%20Here's%20what%20you%20need%20to%20know%20about%20the%20biggest%20recent%20cases%20to%20land%20on%20Google's%20docket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229d068fd7-ebc6-4b84-bda3-32ac78633831%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20did%20the%20US%20government%20sue%20Google%20over%20antitrust%20violations%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20government's%20battle%20against%20Google%20has%20resulted%20in%20two%20major%20antitrust%20cases%20that%20are%20both%20still%20ongoing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20case%20culminated%20in%20a%20landmark%20monopoly%20trial%20in%20the%20fall%20of%202023%2C%20which%20is%20still%20awaiting%20a%20verdict.%20The%20dispute%20centered%20on%20whether%20Google%20has%20illegally%20abused%20its%20monopoly%20over%20the%20search%20engine%20industry%2C%20spending%20billions%20of%20dollars%20each%20year%20to%20suppress%20competition.%20The%20US%20government%20argued%20that%20Google's%20business%20dealings%20have%20blocked%20innovation%20in%20the%20search%20business%20to%20the%20detriment%20of%20internet%20users.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsundar-pichai-google-alphabet-ceo-career-life%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESundar%20Pichai%3C%2Fa%3E%20testified%20in%20the%20antitrust%20trial%20in%20October%202023%2C%20and%20defended%20instances%20in%20which%20Google%20pushed%20companies%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApple%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20other%20smartphone%20makers%20into%20revenue-sharing%20agreements%20that%20would%20make%20Google%20the%20default%20search%20engine%20on%20phones%20and%20computers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Google%20CEO%20Sundar%20Pichai%20smiles%20while%20walking%20past%20security%20personnel%20outside%20a%20federal%20courthouse%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20after%20testifying%20in%20an%20antitrust%20case.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663bee13b4abc992e8c72039%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECEO%20Sundar%20Pichai%20was%20Google's%20star%20witness%20who%20testified%20on%20the%20company's%20deals%20with%20smartphone%20makers%20to%20make%20Google%20the%20default%20search%20engine.%3Cp%3EDrew%20Angerer%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ceo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20CEO%3C%2Fa%3E%20even%20acknowledged%20on%20the%20stand%20that%20company%20executives%20knew%20that%20becoming%20the%20default%20search%20engine%20on%20smartphones%20%26quot%3Bwould%20lead%20to%20increased%20usage%20of%20our%20products%20and%20services.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20major%20antitrust%20case%20against%20Google%20concerns%20its%20online%20advertising%20strategies%2C%20and%20is%20set%20to%20go%20to%20trial%20in%20September%202024.%20The%20US%20government%20has%20alleged%20that%20Google%20illegally%20abused%20its%20monopoly%20over%20the%20digital%20advertising%20market%20by%20acquiring%20its%20competitors%20and%20forcing%20website%20publishers%20to%20adopt%20Google's%20tools%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ads-adwords%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20Ads%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20thereby%20suppressing%20the%20rise%20of%20rival%20technologies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20has%20denied%20any%20wrongdoing%20in%20both%20cases.%20The%20search%20giant%20argued%20during%20its%202023%20trial%20that%20Google%20dominates%20the%20search%20business%20because%20it's%20superior%20to%20its%20rivals%2C%20not%20because%20of%20its%20business%20dealings.%20Google%20has%20similarly%20denied%20the%20claims%20in%20the%20advertising-related%20monopoly%20case%2C%20saying%20its%20acquisitions%20were%20legal%20and%20actually%20enable%20innovative%20new%20advertising%20technologies%2C%20and%20that%20the%20federal%20government's%20lawsuit%20could%20undo%20years%20of%20industry%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a2de7586-71f8-42ee-a300-2b9e1b56ccc4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20happens%20if%20Google%20loses%20its%20antitrust%20cases%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20who%20will%20win%20the%20antitrust%20case%20on%20Google's%20search%20engine.%20Judge%20Amit%20Mehta%20will%20be%20the%20one%20to%20decide%20the%20outcome%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20jury%2C%20and%20Mehta%20vigorously%20questioned%20both%20sides%20during%20closing%20arguments%20in%20May%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-antitrust-trial-big-tech-future-analysis-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20loses%20the%20lawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Mehta%20is%20expected%20to%20take%20some%20sort%20of%20action%20that%20would%20boost%20competition%20in%20the%20search-engine%20business.%20Google%20could%20face%20consequences%20like%20fines%2C%20orders%20to%20adjust%20its%20business%20practices%2C%20or%20even%20a%20total%20ban%20on%20its%20contracts%20to%20make%20Google%20the%20default%20search%20engine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20antitrust%20cases%20carry%20potentially%20massive%20implications%20for%20internet%20users%20%E2%80%94%20Google%20could%20face%20sanctions%20that%20alter%20its%20operations%20so%20dramatically%20that%20it%20loses%20its%20ubiquity%20in%20the%20search%20and%20advertising%20industries%2C%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20new%20companies%20and%20technologies%20to%20flourish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle's%20antitrust%20cases%20will%20also%20likely%20influence%20the%20outcomes%20of%20other%20antitrust%20lawsuits%20the%20US%20government%20has%20filed%20against%20major%20tech%20companies.%20Currently%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Apple%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-business-suite%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%3C%2Fa%3E%20all%20face%20similar%20antitrust%20lawsuits%20against%20their%20business%20practices%20that%20could%20threaten%20their%20market%20dominance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229e1c9831-9b4b-4c83-8898-757900d949af%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20to%20know%20about%20Google's%20class-action%20settlements%20and%20who%20can%20claim%20money%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20has%20been%20the%20subject%20of%20two%20major%20class-action%20lawsuits%20that%20were%20resolved%20or%20nearing%20resolution%20in%20late%202023%20and%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20hotly%20anticipated%20resolutions%20was%20that%20of%20a%20class-action%20case%20involving%20personal%20data%20collected%20from%20136%20million%20Google%20Chrome%20users.%20The%20lawsuit