ride%20(SF6)%2C%20identified%20by%20the%20Intergovernmental%20Panel%20on%20Climate%20Change%20as%20the%20most%20potent%20greenhouse%20gas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20CO2%20remains%20in%20the%20atmosphere%20for%205-200%20years%2C%20SF6%20can%20persist%20for%20anywhere%20between%20600%20to%203%2C200%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20carbon%20removal%20strategies%20only%20eliminate%20about%20two%20billion%20tonnes%20per%20year%20out%20of%20an%20estimated%20requirement%20of%2020%20billion%20tonnes%20to%20balance%20our%20carbon%20emissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20newly%20discovered%20material%20could%20enhance%20direct%20air%20capture%20efficiency%2C%20decrease%20energy%20consumption%20and%20avert%20the%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20see%20this%20study%20as%20an%20important%20step%20towards%20unlocking%20such%20applications%20in%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mr%20Little.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResearchers%20said%20along%20with%20greenhouse%20gases%2C%20the%20new%20material%20can%20also%20remove%20other%20toxic%20fumes%20in%20the%20air%2C%20such%20as%20those%20that%20surface%20inside%20new%20cars.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715324520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2017-10%2Fcarbon-dioxide-emission_650x400_81509360563.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fno-more-pollution-new-material-can-absorb-trap-greenhouse-gases-5630949%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20material%20shows%20excellent%20stability%20in%20water%2C%20which%20makes%20it%20useful%20to%20be%20used%20in%20capturing%20carbon%20in%20industrial%20settings.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fno-more-pollution-new-material-can-absorb-trap-greenhouse-gases-5630949%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fno-more-pollution-new-material-can-absorb-trap-greenho