n%20September%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPune%20police%20initially%20probed%20the%20case.%20The%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI)%20took%20over%20the%20probe%20in%202014%20following%20a%20Bombay%20High%20Court%2C%20order%20and%20arrested%20Dr%20Virendrasinh%20Tawade%2C%20an%20ENT%20surgeon%20linked%20to%20the%20Hindu%20right-wing%20organisation%20Sanatan%20Sanstha%2C%20in%20June%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20prosecution%2C%20Tawade%20was%20one%20of%20the%20masterminds%20of%20the%20murder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESanatan%20Sanstha%2C%20to%20which%20Tawade%20and%20some%20of%20the%20other%20accused%20were%20linked%2C%20was%20opposed%20to%20the%20work%20carried%20out%20by%20Dabholkar's%20organisation%2C%20the%20Maharashtra%20Andhashraddha%20Nirmoolan%20Samiti%20(committee%20for%20eradication%20of%20superstition%2C%20Maharashtra)%2C%20it%20claimed.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715322780000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2016-06%2Fnarendra-dabholkar_650x400_81465618491.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F2-found-guilty-in-activist-narendra-dabholkar-murder-case-get-life-in-prison-5630557%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Two%20people%20were%20today%20sentenced%20to%20life%20imprisonment%20for%20the%202013%20murder%20of%20activist%20Narendra%20Dabholkar.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F2-found-guilty-in-activist-narendra-dabholkar-murder-case-get-life-in-prison-5630557%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F2-found-guilty-in-activist-narendra-dabholkar-murder-case-get-life-in-prison-5630557%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F2-found-guilty-in-activist-narendra-dabholkar-murder-case-get-life-in-prison-5630557%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Convict%20Can't%20Get%20Parole%20To%20Keep%20Relationship%20With%20Live-In%20Partner%3A%20Court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20has%20held%20that%20Indian%20law%2C%20including%20the%20Delhi%20Prison%20Rules%2C%20does%20not%20permit%20the%20grant%20of%20parole%20to%20a%20convict%20solely%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20maintaining%20a%20conjugal%20relationship%20with%20a%20live-in%20partner%2C%20especially%20when%20the%20convict%20is%20already%20legally%20married.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Swarana%20Kanta%20Sharma%20said%20that%20parole%20cannot%20be%20granted%20to%20a%20convict%20on%20grounds%20of%20having%20a%20child%20or%20maintaining%20conjugal%20relationships%20with%20a%20live-in%20partner%20when%20the%20convict%20has%20a%20legally%20wedded%20wife%20and%20children%20born%20from%20that%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGranting%20such%20parole%2C%20the%20court%20cautioned%2C%20would%20set%20a%20detrimental%20precedent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court's%20observations%20came%20while%20dismissing%20a%20plea%20by%20a%20murder%20convict%20seeking%20parole%20to%20consummate%20his%20marriage%20with%20his%20live-in%20partner%20and%20to%20maintain%20social%20ties.%20The%20convict%20failed%20to%20disclose%20his%20existing%20marriage%20and%20children%20from%20his%20first%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Sharma%20said%20that%20a%20live-in%20partner%2C%20lacking%20legal%20recognition%20as%20a%20spouse%2C%20does%20not%20fall%20within%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20definition%20of%20%26quot%3Bfamily%26quot%3B%20under%20the%20Delhi%20Prison%20Rules%2C%20which%20include%20grandparents%2C%20parents%2C%20siblings%2C%20spouse%2C%20children%2C%20and%20grandchildren.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20acknowledging%20the%20personal%20choices%20and%20relationships%20of%20individuals%2C%20the%20court%20clarified%20that%20it%20doesn't%20interfere%20in%20the%20personal%20lives%20of%20adults%20unless%20there%20are%20criminal%20complaints.%20However%2C%20when%20such%20matters%20come%20before%20the%20court%20seekin